        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 6:16PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 616 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Castella, or 9 miles south of Mount Shasta, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Castella.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
